  "notes": [
    {
      "title": "The Subjunctive Mood (المضارع المنصوب)",
      "titleArabic": "المضارع المنصوب",
      "content": [
        "The subjunctive mood (منصوب) is one of three moods of the present tense verb. It is triggered by certain particles and changes the final vowel from dammah to fathah.",
        "The main particles that cause the subjunctive are: أَنْ (that/to), لَنْ (will not), كَيْ (in order to), and لِـ (for/to)."
      ],
      "keyPoints": [
        "أَنْ - 'that' or 'to' (before verbs): أُرِيدُ أَنْ أَذْهَبَ (I want to go)",
        "لَنْ - 'will not' (negates future): لَنْ يَكْتُبَ (He will not write)",
        "كَيْ - 'in order to': جَاءَ كَيْ يَدْرُسَ (He came to study)",
        "لِـ - 'in order to' / 'for': جَاءَ لِيَدْرُسَ (He came to study)",
        "The verb ending changes: يَذْهَبُ → أَنْ يَذْهَبَ"
      ],
      "examples": [
        { "arabic": "أُرِيدُ أَنْ أَذْهَبَ", "english": "I want to go" },
        { "arabic": "لَنْ يَكْتُبَ", "english": "He will not write" },
        { "arabic": "جَاءَ لِيَتَعَلَّمَ", "english": "He came to learn" }
      ]
    },
    {
      "title": "لَنْ for Future Negation",
      "titleArabic": "لَنْ للنفي المستقبلي",
      "content": [
        "The particle لَنْ negates future actions emphatically. It is stronger than لَا for negation."
      ],
      "keyPoints": [
        "لَنْ + مضارع منصوب = strong future negation",
        "لَنْ أَنْسَى (I will never forget)",
        "Different from لَا يَفْعَلُ which is weaker present negation"
      ]
    }
  ],
